cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper deals with Natural Language Processing (NLP) and specifically Word Sense Disambiguation (WSD) using a deep learning approach. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a single Bidirectional Long Short-Term Memory (BLSTM) network, which is a popular deep learning architecture, indicating a possible fit for cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the need for more training data, suggesting a possible fit for cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed model on a benchmark dataset, indicating a possible fit for cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
